            "subject": "Credit Note Application Policy",
            "body_plain": "When applying credit notes:\n\n1. Match credits to the oldest unpaid invoice for that customer\n2. If the credit exceeds the invoice amount, apply only up to the invoice balance\n3. CRITICAL: Credit notes in DRAFT status CANNOT be allocated. They must be moved to AUTHORISED status first. If a credit note is still in DRAFT, skip it and note it in the customer notification as pending.\n4. Do NOT apply credits to invoices that are already PAID\n5. Notify the customer with the invoice number, credit applied, and remaining balance\n6. Credit limit changes require Credit Committee approval and a formal review. Do NOT modify credit limits during credit allocation.\n\n- Controller",
